{"displayTopicName":"ה interrogative particle","topicTokens":[{"text":"ה interrogative particle","type":"text"}],"paragraphsBySubtopic":{"ה interrogative particle":[{"text":"Hebrew has a ה prefix that turns a given sentence into a question.\n","type":"text"},{"topLevelNodes":[{"ordinal":"-","ordered":false,"tokensOfLine":[{"text":"In traditional grammar it is called the ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"hei hashayla","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ה\"א השאלה, “question ה.”","type":"text"}],"children":[]},{"ordinal":"-","ordered":false,"tokensOfLine":[{"text":"This is not to be confused with the ","type":"text"},{"text":"Hebrew ה prefix meaning “the”","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Hebrew ה prefix meaning “the”","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Hebrew_definite_article","enclosingTopic":"ה interrogative particle","enclosingSubtopic":"ה interrogative particle"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"children":[]},{"ordinal":"-","ordered":false,"tokensOfLine":[{"text":"An example of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"hei hashayla","type":"text"}]},{"text":" would be הֲיֵ֣שׁ לָכֶ֣ם אָ֔ח, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"hayesh lechem ach","type":"text"}]},{"text":". Alone, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"yesh lechem ach","type":"text"}]},{"text":", יֵ֣שׁ לָכֶ֣ם אָ֔ח would mean “you all have a brother.” With the ה prefix, it means “do you all have a brother?”","type":"text"}],"children":[]},{"ordinal":"-","ordered":false,"tokensOfLine":[{"text":"The ה question prefix is usually vowelized as -הֲ, “ha.”","type":"text"}],"children":[]},{"ordinal":"-","ordered":false,"tokensOfLine":[{"text":"Sometimes the ה question prefix is found as a standalone word, הַאִם, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"ha’im","type":"text"}]},{"text":" which begins a question.","type":"text"}],"children":[]}],"type":"outline"}]}}